The court case against Economic Freedom Fighters leader Julius Malema has been postponed in the Newcastle Magistrate’s Court. Malema stands accused of inciting supporters to invade land. The case will be back in court in February 2019. After the case was postponed, the EFF leader addressed supporters outside the court. More to follow. READ MORE: ‘Bring it on bloody racists… I’m born ready!’ - Malema #LandOccupation Malema: Today every worker abused by a white racist or an Indian racist can run to the EFF for help because we have political power. — News24